“I didn’t mean to eat the last cookie,” Peter finally said.

“Should have thought about that sucker,” you said glaring at him.

summary: Get me Kamala Khan and Peter Parker
question: Get me Kamala Khan and Peter Parker
answer:
Superhero relationships were weird. Some superhero teams didn’t like other superhero teams and they fought each other and it was too much for Peter to keep track of so… he just tended to save everyone without thinking about what side they were on. 

Peter wasn’t sure who this girl wearing something that looked like some kind of superhero costume but she was falling off of a building and Peter didn’t know if she had powers that could save her so he immediately dove for her.  

“Hi!” Peter greeted as he caught her and shot a web to swing to a safer place. 

“Holy- Spider-Man?” She exclaimed excitedly. Peter’s heart jumped at her excitement, he didn’t know too many people that were genuinely fans of him, at least that weren’t much smaller than this teenage girl. He honestly loved the attention. 

“Are there any other spider-themed superheroes? wait…” Peter carefully dropped them on the ground and let go of the girl. 

“Only a few.” The girl giggled. “Uh, thanks. I don’t normally fall off of buildings”

“Oh, I hope not.” Peter chuckled. “So what’s your gig? You look like you just got ready for ComicCon.” 

“Ha ha… I’m K- I mean Ms. Marvel. I do have powers, I didn’t just decide to do dumb things all the time.” 

“Nice to meet you, Ms. Marvel!” Peter heard the distant sound of sirens. “ Unfortunately I can’t stay for very long, wanna team up sometime?”

“Anytime I’m in the area I guess.” She smiled. 

“Bye! Don’t jump off of any buildings without me!” Peter jumped off of the roof and started to swing away, not before hearing a quiet ‘ohmygod-’ from his new superhero friend. 

He ended up seeing her again, being a superhero made it not too hard for that kind of stuff.

title: Baby Squirrels
body:
So, I read that Squirrels don’t know by nature to avoid people. That behavior is learned, whether by experience or parental instruction. Young squirrels are known to approach humans; especially when separated from their family. A squirrel that doesn’t know better may move towards human activity in search of food, shelter, or warmth; just seeking out what it instinctively wants. Especially in the colder months, little Squirrels that have lost their parents seek out humans especially, in the hope to be protected and cared for.

Can you imagine Peter just adopting every tiny Squirrel he comes across and smuggling them all to the Tower/Compound? And Tony’s inevitable reaction to his home turning into a freaking wildlive reserve.
